---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SafetyCallout from '../../components/SafetyCallout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="For Men" 
  description="Support and guidance for men experiencing relationship conflict, accusations, threats, isolation, or emotional volatility"
>
  <section class="hero-section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="hero-label">For Men</span>
      <h1>You're Not Alone.<br/>And You're Not Crazy.</h1>
      <p class="hero-desc">If you're walking on eggshells, being accused of things you didn't do, or feeling like nothing you do is ever right‚Äîthis resource is for you.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/start-here" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Take the Assessment</a>
        <a href="#what-brings-you" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="what-brings-you">
    <div class="container container-content">
      <h2>What Brings Men Here</h2>
      <p>Men come to this site for many reasons. You might recognize some of these:</p>
      
      <div class="reason-grid">
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h4>Constant Accusations</h4>
          <p>"She says I'm cheating, lying, hiding something. I'm not. But nothing I say convinces her."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h4>Walking on Eggshells</h4>
          <p>"I never know what will set her off. I've learned to be careful about everything I say."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h4>Isolation</h4>
          <p>"I've lost touch with friends and family. She gets upset if I spend time with anyone else."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h4>Monitoring & Control</h4>
          <p>"She checks my phone, my email, tracks my location. She says it's because she doesn't trust me."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h4>Nothing Is Ever Enough</h4>
          <p>"No matter how hard I try, it's never right. The goalposts always move."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h4>Confusion About Reality</h4>
          <p>"Sometimes I wonder if I'm the problem. Maybe I really am as bad as she says."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="mt-lg">If these resonate, you're in the right place. This isn't about blame‚Äîit's about clarity, safety, and skills.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container container-content">
      <h2>Why Men Often Don't Recognize It</h2>
      <p>Research shows that men in difficult or abusive relationships often don't recognize what's happening. Here's why:</p>
      
      <ul class="insight-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Abuse is framed as female victimhood.</strong> Most awareness campaigns show men as perpetrators, women as victims. This makes it hard for men to see themselves as experiencing abuse.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Non-physical abuse is minimized.</strong> "At least she doesn't hit me" is a common thought. But emotional, psychological, and coercive control cause real harm‚Äîsometimes more lasting than physical abuse.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Men are taught to "handle it."</strong> Cultural expectations make men reluctant to admit they're struggling in their relationship, let alone being mistreated.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The frog in boiling water.</strong> When things escalate slowly, each new normal seems like a minor shift from the last. Looking back, the cumulative change is dramatic.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Fear of losing children.</strong> Men often stay because they're afraid of custody outcomes if they leave or speak up.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Shame.</strong> "How did I end up here?" Shame keeps men silent and isolated.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-content">
      <h2>What We Offer</h2>
      
      <div class="offering-grid">
        <div class="offering-card">
          <div class="offering-icon">üîç</div>
          <h4>Clarity</h4>
          <p>Understand what's happening in your relationship. Learn the difference between normal conflict and harmful patterns.</p>
          <a href="/learn/what-is-abuse">Learn About Abuse ‚Üí</a>
        </div>
        <div class="offering-card">
          <div class="offering-icon">üõ°Ô∏è</div>
          <h4>Safety First</h4>
          <p>If you're in danger, we'll help you find resources. Your safety matters‚Äîeven if you've been told it doesn't.</p>
          <a href="/get-help">Get Help Now ‚Üí</a>
        </div>
        <div class="offering-card">
          <div class="offering-icon">üß∞</div>
          <h4>Practical Tools</h4>
          <p>De-escalation techniques, boundary scripts, documentation methods‚Äîskills you can use right now.</p>
          <a href="/tools/de-escalation">View Toolkit ‚Üí</a>
        </div>
        <div class="offering-card">
          <div class="offering-icon">üìö</div>
          <h4>Understanding</h4>
          <p>Learn about trauma responses, hormonal influences, and why people behave the way they do‚Äîwithout excusing harm.</p>
          <a href="/learn/trauma-responses">Learn More ‚Üí</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SafetyCallout type="safety">
    <strong>Are You Safe Right Now?</strong> If you're experiencing threats, intimidation, or fear for your safety, please reach out. The National Domestic Violence Hotline (1-800-799-7233) serves men too. <a href="/get-help">More resources here</a>.
  </SafetyCallout>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container container-content">
      <h2>Common Questions Men Ask</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Can men be abused?</h4>
          <p>Yes. Research indicates that approximately 1 in 7-9 men in the U.S. have experienced severe physical violence by an intimate partner. When including all forms of intimate partner violence (physical, psychological, coercive control, stalking), the numbers are higher. Men underreport at significantly higher rates than women‚Äîestimates suggest only 3% of male victims report compared to 18% of female victims.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>What if she says I'm the abuser?</h4>
          <p>This is common in high-conflict relationships. It can be genuinely confusing. Our <a href="/start-here">assessment tool</a> helps you look at specific behaviors rather than labels. The question isn't "who's the bad guy"‚Äîit's "what patterns are present and how do they affect you?"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Is this site anti-women?</h4>
          <p>No. We also have resources for women experiencing abuse. Recognizing that men can be victims doesn't minimize women's experiences. Abuse is about behavior, not gender.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Should I leave?</h4>
          <p>That's not our place to say. This site provides information and tools to help you make informed decisions. We're not here to tell you what to do‚Äîwe're here to help you see clearly and stay safe.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>What about the kids?</h4>
          <p>Children are affected by conflict between parents‚Äîeven if they're not directly involved. We have <a href="/for-children">resources for protecting children</a> and understanding how adult conflict impacts them.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-content">
      <h2>What This Site Is Not</h2>
      
      <ul class="not-list">
        <li><strong>Not therapy or legal advice.</strong> This is educational content, not a substitute for professional help.</li>
        <li><strong>Not about labeling your partner.</strong> We don't diagnose anyone. We focus on patterns, behaviors, and impact.</li>
        <li><strong>Not about winning.</strong> This isn't ammunition for arguments. It's about your wellbeing and safety.</li>
        <li><strong>Not one-sided.</strong> We encourage self-reflection too. Understanding what's happening doesn't mean you're perfect.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container container-content">
      <h2>Ready to Start?</h2>
      <p>Our 2-3 minute assessment helps you identify what patterns might be present in your relationship and gives you a personalized starting point.</p>
      <a href="/start-here" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Take the Assessment</a>
      <p class="cta-note">No account needed. Private. No judgment.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-section {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary) 0%, var(--color-primary-dark) 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: var(--space-4xl) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .hero-label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    opacity: 0.9;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  
  .hero-section h1 {
    color: white;
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }
  
  .hero-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-xl);
    opacity: 0.95;
  }
  
  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  
  .hero-actions .btn-outline {
    border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    color: white;
  }
  
  .hero-actions .btn-outline:hover {
    border-color: white;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
  }
  
  .reason-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }
  
  .reason-card {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
  }
  
  .reason-card h4 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }
  
  .reason-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }
  
  .insight-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }
  
  .insight-list li {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  
  .insight-list li strong {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }
  
  .offering-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }
  
  .offering-card {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .offering-icon {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  
  .offering-card h4 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  
  .offering-card p {
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  
  .offering-card a {
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  
  .faq-list {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }
  
  .faq-item {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  
  .faq-item h4 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }
  
  .faq-item p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }
  
  .not-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }
  
  .not-list li {
    padding: var(--space-md) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
  }
  
  .not-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  
  .cta-section {
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .cta-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  
  .cta-section p {
    max-width: 500px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-xl);
  }
  
  .cta-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-md) !important;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero-section h1 {
      font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    }
  }
</style>
